Chandra Asri, Citra Marga, Jasa Marga: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-10-05T01:57:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/chandra-asri-citra-marga-jasa-marga-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  slid 2.4 percent to 3,269.45.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures advanced as much as 3.7
percent to $78.46 a barrel in after-hours trading in  New York ,
rebounding from a three-day slide.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),  Indonesia ’s
biggest listed oil company, fell 2.6 percent to 1,900 rupiah and
PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, declined
2.6 percent to 114 rupiah.  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ): The state-owned nickel and gold
producer allocated 12.61 trillion rupiah ($1.4 billion) for
capital expenditure through 2013, Bisnis Indonesia reported,
citing corporate secretary Bimo Budi Satriyo. Antam climbed 0.7
percent to 1,420 rupiah.  PT Chandra Asri Petrochemical (TPIA IJ): The polypropylene
producer obtained a $465 million loan from seven local and
overseas banks to help fund working capital, the company said in
a statement to the stock exchange. Chandra Asri rose 7.7 percent
to 3,500 rupiah.  PT Citra Marga Nusaphala Persada (CMNP IJ): The toll-road
operator may postpone a plan to issue as much as 1.5 trillion
rupiah of bonds to February 2012 from this year due to market
conditions and the company hasn’t agreed on a price yet for a
toll-road acquisition,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing Finance
Director Indrawan Sumantri. Citra Marga retreated 3.6 percent to
1,360 rupiah.  PT Jasa Marga (JSMR IJ): The government will raise tariffs
on 14 toll roads by 6 percent to 25 percent starting Oct. 7,
Kontan reported, citing Public Works Minister Djoko Kirmanto.
Jasa Marga, Indonesia’s biggest toll-road operator, slid 0.7
percent to 3,650 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  